macro.title: Homebuilder confidence remains low amid economic uncertainty
macro.what: Homebuilder confidence stayed low in November, with 41% reporting price cuts and major builders seeing year-over-year margin declines
macro.why: Supply pipeline sets future inventory and construction activity.
macro.market: Stronger pipeline aids suppliers; oversupply later can weigh on pricing.

macro.title: Mortgage rates are calm as the Fed rate cut debate intensifies
macro.what: Mortgage rates average 6.38% as pending home sales increase 15% year over year, with markets watching for another Fed rate cut.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.
